# Implement Phase 1: 3D Physics Framework

## Goal Description
Start the development of the "Lotto Soccer Team" 3D Match Engine by establishing the core physics layer.
As per `3D_축구_매치_엔진_개발_문서화.md`, the first step is to implement realistic ball ballistics using Unity's PhysX and a custom Magnus effect script.

## User Review Required
> [!NOTE]
> This plan focuses purely on the physics foundation (Ball). It does not yet include AI or Player Movement.

## Proposed Changes

### Assets/Game/Scripts/Physics
#### [NEW] [BallAerodynamics.cs](file:///d:/unity/workspace/로또축구단/Assets/Game/Scripts/Physics/BallAerodynamics.cs)
- Implement `MagnusForce` calculation based on angular velocity and velocity.
- Apply force to the Rigidbody in `FixedUpdate`.
- Expose `magnusCoefficient` for tuning.

#### [NEW] [BallPhysicsConfig.cs](file:///d:/unity/workspace/로또축구단/Assets/Game/Scripts/Physics/BallPhysicsConfig.cs)
- A ScriptableObject or Singleton to hold global physics constants (Air density, etc) if needed, or simply keep it within BallAerodynamics for now. (Standardizing on `BallAerodynamics` first).

### Assets/Game/Prefabs
#### [NEW] [Ball.prefab](file:///d:/unity/workspace/로또축구단/Assets/Game/Prefabs/Ball.prefab)
